This paper deals with fine-grained image classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves unsupervised learning, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) is also a key aspect of this paper, which is a popular technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
